 @jamydoug: I can do both, but Rear Window should be available on TPB (some moron advertised his torrents on my threads month back) and Howards End can be 480p only, it is too long movie for 720p, probably.

@believenu: Don't convert them, burn them on empty DVD as they are for archiving purposes only (to keep your hard-disk at max. 80% full). 

If you need conversion because you need playback on older DVD player which doesn't have MP4 capability - be aware that DVD format is at least 4 times more space consuming (2 hours movie in decent quality barely fit 1 empty DVDR) and quality suffers too much, as in any conversion.

My MP4 are incredibly small already, and I humbly suggest to burn them unchanged, and standalone MP4 players cost nowadays 30$ - it may sound as too much but it is lot cheaper than other options. Find player which have USB input, buy cheap 8$ USB stick (2MB) than transfer files from computer on stick, plug it in player - and watch it from stick directly. My sis have learned doing that in few minutes.
